{
  "texts": [
    "Modern NLP models, particularly Large Language Models (LLMs), have shown remarkable advancements over their predecessors.",
    "LLMs, through self-supervised learning and training on vast datasets, have reached a level where they can mimic human-like responses more effectively.",
    "[16] In the medical sector, LLMs are drawing notable attention, with initial research indicating encouraging outcomes.",
    "For instance, ChatGPT by OpenAI, a prominent LLM, has shown capabilities akin to the passing standards of the United States Medical Licensing Examination (USMLE), suggesting its utility in clinical support.",
    "Furthermore, the ability of LLMs to produce natural language has opened avenues for their use in patient education and information dissemination."
  ]
}